<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Announces Zero Inflation Rate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Announces Zero Inflation Rate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306215994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 2103 
GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Zoran Jasic, speaking in Split 
today, stated that the first phase of the goverment's 
stabilization program has achieved its most important goal, that 
being the reduction of the inflation rate to zero. 
Nevertheless, reports unconfirmed by the ministry state that 
the prices of agricultural products have risen around 20 
percent. Minister Jasic announced that negotiations with the 
International Monetary Fund and the World Bank could result in 
loans of $128 million for reconstruction, although IMF and World 
Bank sources say the talks are continuing. 

</TEXT>

