<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Issues Statement on Munitions Explosion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Issues Statement on Munitions Explosion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406213394 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Political Department of the Croatian Army's 
Split operational zone issued a statement today in connection 
with yesterday's explosion in the military munitions depot at 
Kukuzovac, near Sinj, in which two Croatian Army soldiers were 
killed and one was wounded. The statement says that, following 
an investigation, a commission established that mines and 
explosive devices were stored in the depot in line with the 
regulations on keeping and storing such devices, so that the 
explosion did not spread. The statement also stresses that the 
explosion occurred outside the warehouse, and was caused when an 
explosive device of an unidentified type fell on the ground, 
most probably during transport. The device damaged about 20 
other mines. The Army's investigating judge is continuing the 
inquiry into the incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

