<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajina Protests Over Safety of Negotiators </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajina Protests Over Safety of Negotiators </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0306161294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1414 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0306161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 3 Jun (TANJUG) -- Colonel Lazo Babic, 
commander of the Western Slavonia Corps of the Serb Krajina 
Army, sent a protest letter to General Sharmi, the UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Force] commander for Sector West, over an incident 
that happened at a meeting of Sector West's commissions in Lipik 
yesterday. According to a statement by the Serb Krajina Army's 
Main Headquarters, Croatian General Dzanko threatened to arrest 
one of the official Krajina representatives at the talks, and a 
more serious incident was prevented only through UNPROFOR 
General Vergar's intervention. Voicing serious concern over the 
success of the upcoming talks and the safety of the Krajina 
negotiators, Col. Babic demands the Croatian general's apology 
over the incident that could have unforeseeable consequences. 
He also demands an increased level of security by UNPROFOR at 
future talks' venues. 

</TEXT>

