<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Strike Begins at Katowice Steelworks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Strike Begins at Katowice Steelworks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0406094494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0800 
GMT 4 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0406094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A sit-in began at 0600 this morning at the Katowice 
steelworks. Twelve thousand workers have joined the strike so 
far. All production and support sections of the steelworks are 
at a standstill. The strike is supported by most of the trade 
unions operating at the steelworks. The strike committee, 
appointed by Sierpien-80 [August-80] trade union activists, is 
demanding pay increases of 2,000,000 zloty per month, a 
30-percent bonus and a one-time payment of 3,000,000 zlotys to 
every striking worker. 
  The damping down of the iron blast furnace number 1 has 
begun 
and is expected to be completed by 1500. A rally of all staff 
is planned for 1300. 
  The steelworks' management is still of the opinion that it 
is 
impossible to meet the strikers' demands, as this would quickly 
lead to bankruptcy. The management has announced that it would 
rather resign than give in to the demands. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

