Daily Report 
<DATE1>  2 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Reacts to Meciar Statements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reacts to Meciar Statements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206212694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0206212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Press and Information Department of the Slovak 
Government Office has published its stance on statements made by 
Vladimir Meciar, the HZDS [Movement for a Democratic Slovakia] 
chairman, about the coalition government. The department's 
statement says that Meciar's repeated statements about the 
existence of secret agreements within the current government 
coalition -- according to which the Jozef Moravcik cabinet is 
alleged to have assumed the obligation to fulfill the demands 
outlined in eight points by the political entities representing 
the Hungarian national minority -- have revealed that the HZDS 
is completely under the influence of demagogic lies. 
  In its statement, the Press and Information Department of 
the 
Slovak Government Office once again stresses that there are no 
secret agreements obliging the current government to fulfill the 
above-mentioned number of demands. What does exist is the 
government program statement adopted by the National Council. 
  The statement goes on to stress that the HZDS chairman's 
criticism of the course of privatization is equally self-serving 
and demagogic, as it was his cabinet that slowed down the 
transformation of the economy -- something that resulted in last 
year's results of the Slovak economy being worse than those of 
the Czech economy. 
  The Press and Information Department of the Government 
Office 
concludes its statement reacting to some statements by Vladimir 
Meciar by pointing out that his statements are creating 
preconditions for a radicalization of our society. 

</TEXT>

