<H3> <TI>   Kuna Supersedes Dinar as Legal Tender </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuna Supersedes Dinar as Legal Tender </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606083194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 0800 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0606083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] From today the only legal tender in Croatia is the 
kuna. According to a government decision, the dinar is no 
longer valid for payments but may be exchanged for kuna in banks 
and post offices until the end of the year. 

