<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Socialist Party Holds 41st Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bulgarian Socialist Party Holds 41st Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Videnov Reelected to Supreme Council </H4>

<F P=102> AU0606133094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1300 
GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0606133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zhan Videnov has been reelected chairman of the 
Bulgarian Socialist Party [BSP] Supreme Council. According to 
the Election Commission, 688 delegates voted. Some 640 
supported Videnov. The delegates in the congress hall greeted 
this report with applause. Some 47 delegates voted against 
Videnov and one abstained. The results of the All-Party Control 
Commission election are expected in about 30 minutes. 
  Four prominent socialist deputies of the Alliance for Social 
Democracy failed to gain the minimum required votes -- 50 
percent plus one vote -- which is a condition for entering the 
BSP Supreme Council. Dimitur Yonchev, Velislava Dureva, Rosen 
Karadimov, and Elena Poptomova were not elected by the delegates 
who voted for the supreme party organ membership. Andrey 
Lukanov also failed in the election for membership in the BSP 
Supreme Council. 

</TEXT>

