<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Organizations React to Tudor Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Organizations React to Tudor Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    SRI Denies Alleged Coup Planned </H4>

<F P=102> AU0606195594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1700 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0606195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Romanian Intelligence Service [SRI] has faxed 
us a communique referring to the assertion made in Constanta [on 
3 June] by Corneliu Vadim Tudor [senator and chairman of the 
Greater Romania Party, PRM], during a news conference organized 
in that city by the PRM. According to the communique, the SRI 
press bureau has been authorized to publish the following: 
  The examination of the operational situation and the 
information available in the reference domain does not confirm 
the existence of any intention or real possibility of 
assassinating the Romanian president or restoring the monarchy 
in the near future. 
  The circulation of such news without the sufficient previous 
checking of its likelihood needlessly creates confusion and 
unrest or, on the contrary, it makes public opinion doubt the 
seriousness of such assertions. The SRI communique concludes by 
saying that, quote, however, if Senator Corneliu Vadim Tudor is 
in possession of realistic information with respect to the 
aforementioned issue, we invite him to publish it, unquote. 

</TEXT>

