<H3> <TI>   Socialists, Free Democrats Seek Pact by 24 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialists, Free Democrats Seek Pact by 24 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706114494 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1100 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the coalition negotiations which started today, 
the leaders of the Hungarian Socialist Party [MSZP] and the 
Alliance of Free Democrats decided to set up 10 expert 
committees, Gyula Horn has told journalists. The MSZP chairman 
also said that the two parties want to draw up a coalition 
agreement to serve as the basis for a joint government by 24 
June. As a matter of fact, today's round of coordination talks 
was of a technical nature. The participants drew up a timetable 
for the next talks. On behalf of the MSZP, Imre Szekeres and 
Ferenc Baja are expected to head the committee dealing with the 
government's structure, and Gyorgy Janosi is expected to head 
the working group on the state of the media, our correspondent 
reports from the scene of the talks. 

