<H3> <TI>   `Fierce Artillery Attack' on Gradacac Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce Artillery Attack' on Gradacac Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706092894 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0706092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by the Information Service of 107th Knightly </F>
Motorized Brigade from Gradacac] 
  [Text] A fierce artillery attack on Gradacac has been 
underway since early morning. At 0400 the aggressor began an 
all-out attack. So far today, more than 30 of the 
largest-caliber howitzer shells from Skugric have struck at the 
town center. At the same time, tanks in Turic [words 
indistinct] and Bucje are attacking the town and the surrounding 
area, while 120-mm mortars are literally showering the 
industrial zone and the access roads. Bearing in mind that the 
defense lines, especially in the region of Novalic, Sibovac, and 
Mionica are being attacked from 82-mm mortars together with 
intensified fire from antiaircraft machine guns, antiaircraft 
guns, and infantry arms, this morning has been one of the most 
dramatic of late. 
  While Serbian politicians are supposedly championing peace 
[words indistinct] the fascist policy are savagely attacking the 
civilians of this town. At the time of this dispatch, Gradacac 
is veiled in smoke caused by grenades of the largest calibers. 
For the time being we do not have any reports on possible 
casualties of this attack, which is still underway. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

