<H3> <TI>   Muslims Reportedly Violate Cease-Fire Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Muslims Reportedly Violate Cease-Fire Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0606205694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1759 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0606205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, June 6 (TANJUG) -- Snipers from the 
Moslem-held part of Sarajevo on Monday [6 June] continued to 
fire at Serb parts of the city, violating the agreement on a 
ceasefire on the Sarajevo battlefront, the Sarajevo-Romanija 
Corps of the Bosnian Serb republic army said on Monday. Snipers 
from the Moslem section of Dobrinja-Five and Stupsko Brdo were 
firing at the Serb section of Nedjarici and the Kasindolska 
Street, while they were opening fire from Browning machine-guns 
at the Serb section of Hadzici from their stronghold on Mt. 
Ormanj. 
  Moslem units also contimued to fortify their positions in 
the 
sections of Mojmilo and Debelo Brdo. On Monday, the Moslems 
went on with their attacks launched eight days ago on the 
defence positions of the army of the Bosnian Serb republic 
around Srbobran (formerly Donji Vakuf), said the 1st Krajina 
Corps of the Bosnian Serb republic army. 

</TEXT>

