<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs: Defence Positions `Completely Stable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs: Defence Positions `Completely Stable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506175694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1745 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0506175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zvornik, June 5 (TANJUG) -- Although Bosnian Moslem 
forces, assisted by Bosnian Croats and troops of the regular 
army of the Republic of Croatia, are continuing attacks on the 
territory of the republic of Srpska all Serbian defence 
positions are completely stable and Bosnian Serb army troops 
will continue to resolutely prevent any violation of the 
territory of the republic of Srpska, Bosnian Serb army officials 
said on Sunday [5 June]. 
  Armed provocations by Croats are most frequently reported in 
the valley of the river Sava in north-eastern Bosnia, said the 
sources. The Serb side does not react to provocations but when 
the other side launches offensive actions it uses its legitimate 
right to self-defence, they said. 
  Bosnian Serb forces effictively repulsed several Moslem 
artillery and infantry attacks in the region of Teslic in the 
north-eastern part of Bosnia and one on Mount Ozren. They also 
prevented infiltration of a Moslem terrorist group. Serb parts 
of Sarajevo, especially Ilijas, again came under fire from 
Moslem positions in Sarajevo, said the sources. 
  The ceasefire agreement for the Sarajevo region is also 
being 
violated by continuous sniper and small arms fire from the 
Moslem part of Sarajevo on the Serb suburb of Nedzarici and from 
the central party of the city on Ozren Street, said the Serb 
army sources. 
  Moslem snipers in Sarajevo on Friday severely wounded a 
Russian and a French member of the United Nations Protection 
Force (UNPROFOR) but UNPROFOR has so far not reacted to the 
incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

