<DATE1>  5 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgrade Radio: Muslims Suffer `Major Losses' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belgrade Radio: Muslims Suffer `Major Losses' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0506143294 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0506143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Borisav Djuric] </F>
  [Text] After a fragile lull of several days, the Muslims 
have continued their attacks on the Srbobran [Donji Vakuf] 
front. Members of the 7th Corps of the Muslim army early this 
morning carried out a fierce artillery-infantry attack on the 
Koscani plateau. The fighters of the Army of the Serbian 
Republic were ready for this attack. After fierce fighting, the 
Muslims were repelled, suffering major losses in manpower. On 
the Serbian side, several fighters were wounded slightly. NATO 
aircraft were again the allies of the Muslims, flying low over 
the combat area. 
  It was quieter on other parts of the Srbobran front. In 
fact, this is only a brief lull before a new advance by Islamic 
fundamentalists. It is completely clear that the Muslim 
offensive, which started exactly seven days ago, will continue. 
Although the enemy suffered a large number of casualties in the 
first part of this offensive, the 7th Corps is persistently 
trying to take hold of Serbian territories, even if it means 
over the dead bodies of its soldiers. 
  Although an air raid alarm has been sounded, the enemy 
artillery in Bugojno has not been pounding Srbobran today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

