<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moslem-Croat Attacks Reported in North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moslem-Croat Attacks Reported in North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0506115794 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1131 GMT 5 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0506115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Ttext] Brcko, June 5 (TANJUG) -- Moslem and Croat forces 
are continuing attacks on Serb positions and settlements in 
northern and central Bosnia-Herzegovina despite U.N. efforts to 
reach a comprehensive ceasefire at the Geneva talks. Bosnian 
Serb sources announced on Sunday that local Bosnian Croat troops 
and units of the regular Croatian army from the Orasje region 
(northern Bosnia) on Saturday evening used tanks, 60mm mortars, 
anti-aircraft guns and infantry weapons to attack Serb positions 
eight km south and southwest of Orasje. The attacks failed to 
cause any damage and the Bosnian Serb army held their fire. The 
Moslems continued offensive actions in the region of Srbobra 
(former Donji Vakuf), and Mt. Vlasic (central Bosnia) where they 
are also regrouping and massing reinforcements. In the Vlasic 
front, the Moslems used 128mm light rocket launchers and heavy 
mortars. 

</TEXT>

