<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio Reports Serbs Still in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Radio Reports Serbs Still in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706154994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0706154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Enes Musovic from Gorazde] </F>
  [Excerpt] The 3-km exclusion zone from the center of 
Gorazde has still not been cleared of chetniks. UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Force] neither wants nor has the means to implement 
the NATO ultimatum or UN Security Council Resolution 913. At 
approximately 1800 last night, one fighter of the Bosnian Army 
was seriously wounded in the head inside the 3-km zone. He was 
fired at from the direction of (?Sjenokosa). He was in a 
position that could have only been fired on from inside the 
exclusion zone. UNPROFOR is allowing the Serbs that are not 
carrying any arms to freely enter the suburbs of Fazlagici, 
(?Huljderi), and Zubcici to loot what is still left in these 
settlements. Some 90 Serbs came to (?Huljderi) yesterday. They 
looted houses and loaded everything on tractors. After that, 
they freely passed by the blue helmets. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

