<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Shelling Gradacac </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarajevo Radio: Serbs Shelling Gradacac </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706153694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0706153694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified correspondent] </F>
  [Text] The situation in the Gradacac region was reported 
to be particularly grave this morning. 
  [Correspondent] Tank, howitzer, and mortar projectiles are 
landing on the central part of the town, the industrial zone, 
suburbs, and the surrounding villages. The most active 
aggressor's stronghold is most certainly that on Gornje Krecane, 
from where the aggressor is firing all types of weapons, 
including hill guns. They are targeting Rajska and Lukavac. 
The greatest number of projectiles has landed on civilian 
houses, which were also subjected to the fiercest barrage fire. 
The aggressor is thought to have fired more than 400 shells. 
According to the latest report, three persons were wounded. 
This morning, Gradacac was subjected to the brutal and wild 
chetnik artillery attacks, which were witnessed by the 
representatives of the international forces. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-31254 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu110_i_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-110 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs, Abdic Supporters Reportedly Attacking Bihac </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs, Abdic Supporters Reportedly Attacking Bihac </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806115394 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0806115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Here is Mirza Sadikovic reporting on the 
continuation of the attacks by the joint aggressors in the Bihac 
region: 
  [Begin recording] [Bosnian Serb leader Radovan] Karadzic's 
chetniks carried out provocations with infantry weaponry and 
antiaircraft weapons along all lines in the zone covered by the 
[Bosnian Army's] 5th Corps, and particularly in the Bosanska 
Krupa section of the front. Members of [self-proclaimed leader 
of autonomous province of western Bosnia Fikret] Abdic's 
treacherous paramilitary were in action with antiaircraft 
weapons and heavy machine-guns along all lines of separation 
throughout the night and this morning. They indiscriminately 
shelled (?civilian) villages in the [word indistinct] regions of 
(Strbac), Pecigrad, (Lickovac), and (Skodrovo). Shots and bomb 
explosions could be heard throughout the night on the 
(Strbac)-(?Sturlic) line, which clearly shows that what is 
involved are new clashes between Fikret Abdic's mercenaries and 
(?renegades) with the local population, which no longer accepts 
the [words indistinct] conflict imposed on it. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

