<DOCNO> FBIS4-31261 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu110aa_94002" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-110 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia Peace Talks Continue in Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnia Peace Talks Continue in Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Buha Anticipates Further Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD0706085694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 0826 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0706085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Geneva, June 7 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Serb Foreign 
Minister Aleksa Buha said on Tuesday morning [7 May] that an 
agreement on a cessation of hostilities throughout 
Bosnia-Herzegovina might be signed at another meeting, probably 
at Sarajevo airport, rather than at the current talks in Geneva. 
This is a prediction based on the rather modest results 
produced by bilateral contacts held on Monday by U.N. envoy to 
former Yugoslavia Yasushi Akashi with Bosnia's warring Moslems, 
Serbs and Croats, Buha told TANJUG. He stressed that, in its 
latest proposal submitted to Akashi, the Bosnian Serb delegation 
had offered a cessation of hostilities for a year, whereas the 
Moslem-Croat delegation had asked for a ceasefire of between 
four and six weeks, but not longer. 
  With the widely differing positions the delegations are 
embarking on the second day of the Geneva conference and what 
they hoped late on Monday would be a meeting in plenum. Akashi 
told reporters on Monday evening that a ceasefire agreement 
might be signed on Tuesday, with luck. 
  Bosnian Serb President Radovan Karadzic said on Monday that 
the Serb delegation was in favour of a permanent cessation of 
hostilities and was willing to endorse Akashi's plan for a 
four-month ceasefire with slight modifications. Akashi's 
spokesman Michael Williams said he expected the Geneva talks to 
end on Tuesday, but indicated they might continue if agreement 
were not reached. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

