<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia Peace Talks Continue in Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnia Peace Talks Continue in Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ganic on Talks With Butrus-Ghali </H4>

<F P=102> AU0706153294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0706153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Ejup Ganic, vice president of the Federation </F>
of Bosnia-Herzegovina, in Geneva; date not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] The talks with Butrus Butrus-Ghali were very 
interesting because Europe is celebrating D-Day, the day when it 
united itself against fascism and against Hitler. 
Unfortunately, we here in Geneva are holding talks with those 
who have started fascism, and I think the United Nations should 
draw a parallel between these two days, today and the day that 
is being celebrated in Europe -- this is very euphoric -- the 
day when all forces united against Hitler. However, they have 
allowed the Belgrade fascism to promote its ideas here in the 
heart of Europe. 
  Butrus-Ghali said that the United Nations has had many 
problems recently. Problems are appearing everywhere. Of 
course, we have stressed that this is, above all, the 
responsibility of the United Nations, which did not act 
preventively and did not stop the ethnic cleansing and genocide 
in Bosnia. They have verified and bred the virus of ethnic 
cleansing that is now spreading throughout the world. I think 
the situation is very alarming and that the United Nations must 
demonstrate consistency in Bosnia; it must stop fascism to 
somehow regain its credibility and do something in other parts 
of the world. 
  The talks are continuing. Of course, the aggressor is using 
the tactics of freezing. It wants the United Nations to protect 
the territories that it has captured as well as its trenches on 
the front lines; its soldiers are tired and are demanding to be 
replaced. However, we will not agree to that. The negotiations 
are still going on. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-31266 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu110aa_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-110 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

