<H3> <TI>   Katowice Strike Results in Heavy Losses </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Katowice Strike Results in Heavy Losses </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806094494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0100 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Justyna Matyskiewicz, head of the Katowice 
Steelworks information office, has announced that, during the 
first six days of the strike, the plant suffered losses 
amounting to 40.78 billion zlotys [Z]. According to her, each 
subsequent day of the strike will result in further losses of 
about Z10 billion. 
  Late last night, the strike committee began talks with the 
board of the steelworks. The talks are not being conducted 
face-to-face but, rather, through mediators from the Ministry 
for Ownership Transformations. There are signs that an 
agreement can eventually be reached. 

</TEXT>

