<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajina Leaders To Hold Talks With Croatia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajina Leaders To Hold Talks With Croatia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706192994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1739 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, 7 Jun (TANJUG) -- Serb Krajina President 
Krajina Milan Martic today told the TANJUG reporter in Geneva 
that negotiations on economic issues between Croatia and the 
republic of Serb Krajina would be held on 16 and 17 June in 
Plitvice. 
  This has been agreed with the Croatian side, Martic said. 
This afternoon he talked in the Palace of Nations with special 
UN envoy Yasushi Akashi and cochairmen of the Conference on the 
Former Yugoslavia Owen and Stoltenberg. Martic said that in 
Plitvice, talks will take place on economic issues regardless of 
the unresolved political problems with Croatia. He confirmed 
that there was full solidarity between the people of the 
republic of Serb Krajina and their brethren in the republic of 
Srpska and added that the Sava corridor was of vital importance 
to them. The president of the republic of Serb Krajina also said 
that his delegation might talk to UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali tomorrow in the Palace of Nations in Geneva. 
  At a later news conference, Owen and Stoltenberg described 
today's talks as a small step in the right direction and added 
that the next round of talks with the leaders of the republic of 
Serb Krajina would take place on 30 June. They did not specify 
the site or the agenda. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

