<H3> <TI>   General: Army Blundered in Forming Army Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General: Army Blundered in Forming Army Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706125094 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 3 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0706125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "There Will Be a General Staff"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--The transformation of the Army Command 
of the Slovak Republic into the General Staff is being pursued 
within the framework of the first stage of implementing the 
Concept of Building the Army of the Slovak Republic up to the 
Year 2000. This change should be carried out this year but no 
later than next year, Major General Julius Humaj, commander of 
the Army of the Slovak Republic, told the TA SR yesterday. 
Following experience with a similar arrangement of West 
European armies, the change will mainly affect internal 
organizational structures. General Humaj described the 
formation of the Army Command as one of the mistakes made in 
drafting the concept and structure of the newly established 
Republic's armed forces. 

</TEXT>

