<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Indian-Slovak Enterprise"] </F>
  [Text] The Tatra Sipox a.s. [shareholding company] at 
Banovce nad Bebravou and BEML, the largest Indian manufacturer 
of military equipment, reached a preliminary agreement on the 
founding of a joint venture yesterday. This was announced by 
Jozef Majsky, president of Tatra Sipox a.s., and confirmed by M. 
Mallikarjun, Indian minister of state for defense. The joint 
venture will produce trucks using Indian engines and Tatra 
chassis and cabins. They will be assembled partly in Slovakia 
and partly in India. 
  [Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak on 3 June on page 2 
carries a 100-word report on the Indian minister's visit to 
Banovce nad Bebravou, which quotes Tatra Sipox President Majsky 
as saying that the joint venture should produce "at least 2,000 
vehicles a year over a period of five years."] 

