<H3> <TI>   Dukovany Permitted To Store Spent Nuclear Fuel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dukovany Permitted To Store Spent Nuclear Fuel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706125694 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1000 
GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry for Economy has confirmed granting 
permission to build a storage depot for spent nuclear fuel at 
the Dukovany nuclear power station. According to the power 
station's press spokesman, Petr Spilka, today, no appeal against 
this decision is possible. Thus, following three years of 
administrative procedures, the Dukovany power station will be 
able to start building. Preparatory works on the construction 
will start as early as this week. The storage depot will house 
60 containers containing 600 tonnes of spent nuclear fuel, which 
should be transferred to the projected central in-process store 
[centralni mezisklad] by the year 2005. 

</TEXT>

