<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Warns of Italian Neofascist Claims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman Warns of Italian Neofascist Claims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706154094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Top-level Slovene-Croat talks have been held in 
the Presidential Palace in Zagreb. The presidents of the two 
countries, Franjo Tudjman and his guest Milan Kucan, who arrived 
this morning for a working visit to Croatia, made brief 
statements following their talks. The Slovene president's visit 
to Zagreb is being covered by Andjelko Perincic: 
  [Perincic] Speaking to the press, President Kucan described 
the talks as tough, polemic, and open but imbued with mutual 
understanding nevertheless. 
  [Begin Kucan recording, in Slovene with superimposed 
Serbo-Croatian translation] I believe, as the talks 
demonstrated, that unilateral solutions do not facilitate mutual 
understanding and the development of mutual trust between the 
two countries. The talks were held under different 
circumstances from those surrounding the process of securing 
Slovene and Croatian independence when there were intense 
contacts. [end recording] 
  Kucan also said life demands solutions to problems and the 
establishment of new political relations can be endorsed only by 
concrete steps. Croatian President Franjo Tudjman also spoke to 
the press. 
  [Begin Tudjman recording] Many international factors prompt 
both Croatia and Slovenia to coordinate their policies. The 
rise of neofascist claims in today's Italy against Slovene and 
Croatian territory explicitly point to this. Understandably, we 
hope the Italian Government will continue the democratic 
policies pursued by the previous governments and the policy of 
friendly relations with our countries. At the same time we must 
not ignore those forces that are openly extolling fascism, 
including everything this fascism brought about on the soil of 
Slovenia and Croatia. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

