<H3> <TI>   U.S. President's Special Envoy Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. President's Special Envoy Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706165694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1113 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ohrid, 7 Jun (TANJUG) -- Matthew Nimetz, special 
envoy of the U.S. President in the Macedonia [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM]-Greece dispute, arrived 
on a two-day working visit to Macedonia today to hold talks in 
connection with the resumption of the New York negotiations 
between Athens and Skopje on 13 June. Nimetz, who arrived from 
Athens, was welcomed at Ohrid's Podmolje airport by FYROM 
Foreign Minister Stevo Crvenkovski and Ivan Tosevski, an 
official of this ministry. Nemitz and Crvenkovski immediately 
started talks in Ohrid. The U.S. envoy will be received in 
Skopje tomorrow by FYROM President Kiro Gligorov. 

</TEXT>

