<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kosovo Albanians Charged With Threatening Serbia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kosovo Albanians Charged With Threatening Serbia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0706194994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1307 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0706194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Pristina, 7 Jun (TANJUG) -- The District Public 
Prosecutor's Office in Pristina today charged seven Kosovo 
Albanians with the criminal act of threatening the territorial 
integrity of Serbia and Yugoslavia. 
  Charges were filed against Fehmija Ljestrani, Skeljzen 
Bajrami, Ljuan Heta, Nedzmedin Sadriju, Becir Muljeci, Isni 
Franc, and Bajram Galapani. According to the indictment, during 
the second half of 1992 and last year, while in the Republic of 
Albania, the group "in cooperation with other persons, plotted 
and carried out actions aimed at helping the secession of Kosovo 
and Metohija, and other parts of the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia populated with members of the Albanian minority with 
the ultimate aim of setting up a separate state, and its 
integration with neighboring Albania." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

