<H3> <TI>   Former Border Guards Testify </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Border Guards Testify </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606204894 Tirana ATA in English 1010 GMT 6 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0606204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, June 6 (ATA) -- In yesterday's sitting of 
the trial of 10 former senior officials of the Albanian 
communist system, five witnesses, former employees of the 
Interior Branch of Sarande, gave testimony on the practices used 
in guarding the sea border, the way of realising the imitation 
and procedures carried out to transport drowned corpses who had 
attempted to cross the border. 
  Mithat Bala, Luan Zani, Reiz Maksuti, (non-commissioned 
officers), confessed before the jury that the order for the 
transportation of corpses on board of the motorboat and their 
demonstration was given by the former chairman of the district's 
interior branch, Defendant Veiz Haderi, to show in this way "the 
vigilant guarding of the border." 
  Witness Maqo Como, political prisoner, and former deputy and 
minister, bore testimony of the history of his family in prisons 
and internment, a history which bears the seal of the 
Expulsion-Internment Commission. 
  Zvetllana Marku, the daughter of General Gjin Marku executed 
by the regime of dictator Hoxha, testified to the injustices and 
intolerance of this commission. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

