<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Closure of Border Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Denies Closure of Border Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706180094 Tirana ATA in English 0821 GMT 7 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0706180094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lindita Karadaku] </F>
  [Text] Tirana, June 7 (ATA) -- "The border point of Hani i 
Hotit has not been closed," confirmed the spokesman of the 
Albanian Ministry of Public Order, refuting a report from the 
Automoto League of Former Yugoslavia according to which 
"Albanian bodies do not allow the entry of cars with Yugoslav 
number plates to Albania." The spokesman said that there is a 
strict border control in Hani i Hotit due to the fuel 
trafficking. Several Albanian and Montenegrin citizens involved 
in the traffic have been detained. Control is being made mainly 
for vehicles but this does not hinder the movement of citizens 
from both sides of the border. 

</TEXT>

