<H3> <TI>   Outgoing MDF Issues Statement on Resignation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Outgoing MDF Issues Statement on Resignation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0406202994 Budapest MTI in English 1858 GMT 4 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0406202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, June 4 (MTI) -- At its one-day closed-door 
session on Saturday [4 June], the National Board of the 
Hungarian Democratic Forum [MDF] discussed parliamentary 
election experiences and the party's internal situation. A 
statement issued to the press after the conference, party 
chairman Lajos Fur announced the resignation of the MDF 
Presidium at the party's next special national convention, the 
date for which will be set later on. The statement says, "The 
board considers it necessary to thoroughly examine both the 
party's unsatisfactory election result and its future policy." 
  Spokesman Karoly Herenyi told journalists that the board 
meeting heard over 30 contributions on reasons behind the 
election failure and ways of proceeding ahead. The MDF, 
adapting to current conditions, should shape its policy in a 
different style as an opposition force, it was stated at the 
session. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

