<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Election Result Challenged by MDF Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Election Result Challenged by MDF Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706083294 Budapest MTI in English 1843 GMT 6 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0706083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 6 June (MTI) -- At the request of Gyorgy 
Rasko, who ran for parliamentary deputy on the Hungarian 
Democratic Forum (MDF) ticket in the 6th constituency -- 
Gyor-Sopron County -- and received 10 fewer votes than Gyula 
Varga of the Alliance of Free Democrats (SZDSZ) in the run-off 
elections on May 29, the National Election Committee checked the 
342 invalid votes cast in the constituency and found 68 to be 
valid. 
  Of these, 31 went to Rasko, 21 to Gabor Simon of the 
Hungarian Socialist Party (MSZP), and 16 to Varga. In this way, 
Rasko moved to first place with 9,417 votes, ahead of Varga, who 
thus had 9,412 votes. Simon received 21 additional votes, but 
even so he remained third, with 8,200 votes. 
  At Rasko's request, on Thursday [9 June] afternoon the 
committee will re-examine all 26,000 votes cast in the 
constituency. The MDF would thus send 38 and the SZDSZ 69 
parliamentary deputies to the 386-seat parliament. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

