<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boross Replies to Letter From Bishop Tokes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boross Replies to Letter From Bishop Tokes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0606183294 Budapest MTI in English 1546 GMT 6 Jun 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0606183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 6 June (MTI) -- "I sincerely hope that 
Hungary's new government will not forget its obligations towards 
ethnic Hungarians beyond the border, that it will use all 
possible means -- including international forums -- to further 
their interests, and that it will hold preliminary discussions 
on all related political moves with legitimate leaders of 
cross-border Hungarian organizations beforehand." 
  ``I also hope that the new government will require that 
policy on ethnic Hungarians abroad be invariably based on a 
consensus between parliamentary parties. 
  "I shall be in a position to warn my successor in the post 
of 
prime minister of this obligation," says a letter from Peter 
Boross to Oradea Bishop Laszlo Tokes, which was released by the 
Government Spokesperson's Office to MTI on Monday [6 June]. 
  Boross was replying to Tokes's open letter, published in the 
Budapest daily MAGYAR NEMZET on April 11, asking for Hungary's 
political support for Transylvanian Hungarians, urging the 
conclusion of a bilateral cooperation accord between the 
Hungarian Government and the Hungarian Democratic Federation of 
Romania, and calling for political and economic assistance to 
curb the emigration of Hungarians from Transylvania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-31329 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu110__a94010" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-110-A </AU>
