<H3> <TI>   Deputies Pass Article on Education in Romanian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputies Pass Article on Education in Romanian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0206203194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1646 GMT 2 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0206203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 2/6/1994 -- Deputies endorsed by 
vote on June 2 Article 8 of the Education Bill, which stipulates 
that education of all grades shall proceed in Romanian. It was 
also established that the study and learning of the Romanian 
language as the official language in the state shall be 
compulsory for all Romanian citizens, irrespective of 
nationality. 
  After contradictory discussions, the deputies rejected the 
amendments promoted by Varujan Vosganian (Armenians' Union of 
Romania) and Benedek Nagy (Democratic Union of Hungarians in 
Romania) protesting the introduction of this article, which 
belongs to the general principles of expressing provisions on 
the education in the mother tongues of the nationalities and in 
the languages of international circulation [sentence as 
received]. The amendments were assessed as "overzealous," 
especially considering that by the same article the deputies 
voted in favor of guaranteeing the right of persons belonging to 
ethnic minorities to study and get instructed in their mother 
tongue, and the education bill gives special attention to this 
issue in other articles. 

</TEXT>

