<H3> <TI>   Serb `Campaign of Barbarian Attacks' Protested </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb `Campaign of Barbarian Attacks' Protested </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0506174594 Tirana ATA in English 0833 GMT 5 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0506174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, June 4 (ATA) -- The recent campaign of 
barbarian attacks of the Serbian authorities and violence 
against the Kosova institutions and against all the Albanian 
organizations, accompanied by detention, imprisonments and 
sentences have caused indignation and protest all over Kosova. 
  The common message of all those protests and reactions is to 
continue the work and the activity of institutions in the 
republic of Kosova against the persecutions, violence, grave 
conditions under the occupation and to continue persistently the 
development in other new fields of the institutional 
organization of the life. 
  The protests emphasise that the Serbian tendency for 
discriminating the activity of those institutions by calling 
them illegal and parallel only because they are legal and 
opposite to the violence organs, is unacceptable and fleeting. 
The organizing of the political, state, and institutional life 
in Kosova finds a complete support in the legal and natural 
right which is the political will of the Kosova people expressed 
in a democratic way by the referendum for independence, first 
pluralist, parliamentary, and presidential elections, as it is 
said in the reactions. 

</TEXT>

