<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO's Quaddumi Visits, Signs Protocol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO's Quaddumi Visits, Signs Protocol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0706181094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1300 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0706181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Teodor Melescanu, Romanian minister of foreign 
affairs, and Faruq Qaddumi, head of the PLO Political 
Department, signed a protocol this afternoon on cooperation 
between the Romanian Government and the PLO Executive Committee. 
After signing the document, the Romanian foreign minister said 
that the protocol is an expression of the Romanian Government's 
desire to continue to stay involved in supporting the peace 
process in the Middle East. At the same time, he said, the 
protocol provides a principled foundation for Romania's direct 
participation in the reconstruction and development of Gaza and 
Jericho. 
  Melescanu also handed Qaddumi a letter addressed by the 
Romanian Government to Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, which emphasizes 
Romania's determination to contribute to the economic 
reconstruction of the autonomous Palestinian territories with 
the offer of 50 scholarships for Palestinian students wishing to 
study priority economic subjects in Romania. 
  In his turn, Qaddumi said that the document signed today 
marks a new stage in Romanian-Palestinian cooperation and will 
consolidate bilateral cooperation to the end of establishing 
peace and stability in the Middle East. This report was sent in 
to us by our correspondent Eugen Baboi. 
  Qaddumi was also received by President Ion Iliescu at 
Cotroceni Palace. During the talks the sides tackles issues 
pertaining to the latest developments in the Middle East. On 
this occasion, President Ion Iliescu was conveyed wishes for 
well-being from Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, the Palestinian guest 
told the press after the meeting. In connection with the 
document signed today at the Romanian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs, Qaddumi said that Romania is the first country in 
Eastern Europe with which such an agreement is signed. He added 
that this agreement is very important for intensifying bilateral 
relations. 
  The meeting between President Ion Iliescu and the PLO 
official was attended by Romanian Foreign Minister Melescanu and 
by Presidential Adviser Traian Chebeleu. 

</TEXT>

