BFN 

  [Excerpt] Skopje, 8 Jun (TANJUG) -- In Skopje today, 
Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
President Kiro Gligorov today received Matthew Nimetz, the 
special U.S. envoy in the Greek-Macedonian dispute. Their talks 
lasted for more than two hours. Nimetz arrived on a two-day 
working visit to the FYROM yesterday ahead of the resumption of 
negotiations between Skopje and Athens in New York on 13 June. 
  In a press statement following his talks with Gligorov, 
which 
were also attended by Macedonian Foreign Relations Minister 
Stevo Crvenkovski, Nimetz said that he spoke about the topics of 
great importance for regional developments. According to 
Nimetz, it is inappropriate to give any forecasts as regards the 
outcome of future negotiations. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

